  "why": "The paper goes beyond merely reporting failures: it characterizes failure patterns (state coverage, distinct crash types, spatial distributions), defines a robustness measure for seeds, ablates the curiosity component to show its effect, and uses discovered crashes to repair a model (ACAS Xu) with empirical reduction in failures. These analyses give partial diagnostic insight into where and how failures occur (statistical / sensitivity patterns and epistemic uncertainty via the curiosity predictor). However, the paper does not trace failures to underlying model vulnerabilities such as corrupted or biased training data, reliance on spurious features, or structural overfitting, nor does it provide empirical evidence linking discovered failures to such root causes; repairs are performed via manual inspection and fine-tuning rather than systematic causal analysis. This corresponds to the “Medium” level: partial diagnostic insight based on failure patterns and model-behavioral signals, without linking failures to underlying vulnerabilities.",
